[Essentially identical reports have been made by other news services, presumably from the same official news release:
http://www.dailystar.com.lb/News/World/2014/Jul-04/262627-five-in-hungary-examined-for-suspected-anthrax-infection.ashx
https://news.yahoo.com/five-people-hungary-monitored-suspected-anthrax-infection-073237978--sector.html

To find Tiszafured, go to: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tiszaf%C3%BCred. This is in Jasz-Nagykun-Szolnok county, which has suffered singular sporadic outbreaks in sheep in 2009 (9 sheep affected) and 2013 (6 affected). As a threshold number of sheep have to be dead before the owner will contact his veterinarian, we can assume that outbreaks limited to 1-2 sheep are not being reported. This infrequency can result in mistaken and missed diagnoses and regrettable behaviour. Hopefully this "frozen meat" event will result in some more proactive surveillance and vaccination. (Thanks to Sabine for this report.) - Mod.MHJ]
